<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,757,2007]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,757,783]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species (
<figureCitation box="[430,563,757,784]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–28" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[176,1412,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-32@14.[176,1412,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 18–28. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 18, 19, C. discalis, holotype male. 18, dorsal aspect. 19, lateral aspect. 20–22, C. elutipes. 20, male, dorsal aspect. 21, female, dorsal aspect. 22, female, lateral aspect. 23, 24, C. femoralis, lectotype male. 23, dorsal aspect. 24, lateral aspect. 25, 26, C. fiuzai. 25, male, dorsal aspect. 26, female, dorsal aspect. 27, 28, C. glabratus, holotype male. 27, dorsal aspect. 28, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646371/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs. 25, 26</figureCitation>
) is distinguished by the brownish-orange embolium, apical area of the corium, outer two thirds of the cuneus, and posterior area of the pronotal disc; the uniformly yellowish-white antenna and legs, including the coxae; and the broad, apically rounded right paramere (
<figureCitation box="[985,1069,829,855]" captionStart="Figures 71– 84" captionStartId="40.[151,232,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,412,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-92@40.[170,1418,412,1862]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figures 71– 84. Male genitalia of Cyrtocapsus spp. 71, 72, C. fiuzai. 71, left paramere. 72, right paramere. 73, 74, C. glabratus. 73, left paramere. 74, right paramere. 75, 76, C. grenadensis. 75, left paramere. 76, right paramere. 77–79, C. haitianus. 77, left paramere. 78, endosoma. 79, right paramere. 80, 81, C. intermedius. 80, left paramere. 81, right paramere. 82–84, C. lazelli. 82, left paramere. 83, endosoma. 84, right paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646385" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646385/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,757,2007]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName box="[199,399,865,892]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cyrtocapus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fiuzai">
<emphasis box="[199,399,865,892]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Cyrtocapus fiuzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1909" box="[552,718,865,892]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[552,718,865,892]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">C. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[735,818,865,891]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–39" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-16@27.[170,1418,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 29–39. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 29, 30, C. grenadensis. 29, male, dorsal aspect. 30, female, dorsal aspect. 31, C. guianus, holotype female, dorsal aspect. 32, 33, C. haitianus. 32, male dorsal aspect. 33, female, dorsal aspect. 34, C. intermedius, female, dorsal aspect. 35, 36, C. lazelli. 35, male, dorsal aspect. 36, female, dorsal aspect. 37, 38, C. marginatus. 37, lectotype male, dorsal aspect. 38, paralectotype female, dorsal aspect. 39, C. mesoamericanus, holotype male, dorsal aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646373/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) in sharing the brownish-orange embolium and apical areas of the corium and pronotum, and the pale legs. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1909" box="[731,1008,901,928]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[731,1008,901,928]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Cyrtocapsus intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1152,1245,901,928]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cyrtocapus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fiuzai">
<emphasis box="[1152,1245,901,928]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">C. fiuzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the uniformly dark brown pronotum (or sometimes with the basal margin paler brown); the apically red or dark reddish-brown apex of the antennal segment II (rather than uniformly yellowish white); and the distinctly more elongate right paramere (
<figureCitation box="[271,354,1009,1035]" captionStart="Figures 71– 84" captionStartId="40.[151,232,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,412,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-92@40.[170,1418,412,1862]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figures 71– 84. Male genitalia of Cyrtocapsus spp. 71, 72, C. fiuzai. 71, left paramere. 72, right paramere. 73, 74, C. glabratus. 73, left paramere. 74, right paramere. 75, 76, C. grenadensis. 75, left paramere. 76, right paramere. 77–79, C. haitianus. 77, left paramere. 78, endosoma. 79, right paramere. 80, 81, C. intermedius. 80, left paramere. 81, right paramere. 82–84, C. lazelli. 82, left paramere. 83, endosoma. 84, right paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646385" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646385/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
